Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fermin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fermin\"}, {\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villarreal_CF\", \"score\": 0.999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.741655926294017e-11, \"text\": \"Villareal\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villarreal_CF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villarreal_CF\"}, {\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9990478278693466, \"rank\": 0.0009432986954643528, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However the home side could not hold on as Camello bagged two more goals to seal the victory.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before Henry's brief interjection to congratulate him, two-goal hero Camello gave an emotional interview after the game in which he thanked his team-mates and told a story of how he believed he was going to score in the game.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Henry, who is currently the coach of the French Under-21 side took the reins for the Olympic Games following managerial stints with the Belgium national team, Monaco, and Canadian outfit Montreal Impact.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2006, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_under-21_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Under-21\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_under-21_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_under-21_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_foot